SYNOPSIS
        int *shuffle(int A, int B)

DESCRIPTION
	Returns an array of integers from 'A' to 'B' in random order.

EXAMPLE
	int *aiNums = shuffle(1, 10);

        // aiNums will contain the numbers 1-10 in random order within the array
        // eg. '({ 4, 2, 7, 5, 1, 9, 3, 6, 10, 8 })'

SEE ALSO
	random
